---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
    <section class="hero reveal">
        <div class="container reading">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ सत्यमेव जयते ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Advisory Statement</span>
            <h1>Your Business Has a <span class="highlight">Bottleneck</span>.</h1>
            <p style="font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 2rem); font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--accent); margin-top: -0.2rem; font-style: italic; font-weight: 500;">
                You're Probably Fixing the Wrong Thing.
            </p>
            <p class="lead">
                I help Indian businesses identify the real constraint — using <strong style="color: var(--text);">Bharatiya systems thinking</strong> rooted in Sanatan principles. No imported frameworks. Just clarity.
            </p>
            <a href="/work-with-aman/systems-audit" class="btn">Request a Systems Audit</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="reveal" style="padding-top: 60px;">
        <div class="container reading">
            <span class="tag">Pre‑Conditions</span>
            <h2>Common Signs Something Is Broken.</h2>
            <p>You may benefit from a Systems Audit if:</p>
            <ul class="structural reveal-stagger">
                <li>Your website no longer reflects the true quality of your professional work.</li>
                <li>Leads arrive inconsistently or fail to convert clean opportunities.</li>
                <li>Important operating knowledge exists only inside individual people's heads.</li>
                <li>Team members repeatedly ask the same questions due to training fragmentation.</li>
                <li>Daily execution and fulfillment operations depend heavily on specific individuals.</li>
                <li>Information and internal system data are scattered across multiple unlinked tools.</li>
                <li>Growth has introduced heavy operational complexity, overhead weight, and confusion.</li>
                <li>You are entirely unsure what component to stabilize or fix first.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="reveal" style="padding-top: 90px;">
        <div class="container reading">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ योगः कर्मसु कौशलम् ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Analysis Architecture</span>
            <h2>Why I Look at Systems Differently</h2>
            <p class="lead">
                I am Aman. I help Indian businesses understand and improve the permanent systems behind their work — through a <strong style="color: var(--text);">Bharatiya lens</strong>.
            </p>
            <p style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--text);">
                Most businesses respond to problems by forcing additional brute effort. More content. More tools. More meetings. More integrations.
            </p>
            <p>
                Often that creates massive additional liability because the underlying constraint was never identified correctly. The objective is not to build complexity—it is to construct workflows that are understandable, permanent, and capable of supporting growth without human gridlocks.
            </p>
            <div class="axis" id="flowContainer">
                <div class="axis-item active"><span class="arrow">↓</span><span><strong>Reality</strong> — observed without interpretation</span></div>
                <div class="axis-item"><span class="arrow">↓</span><span><strong>Observations</strong> — case studies, evidence, data</span></div>
                <div class="axis-item"><span class="arrow">↓</span><span><strong>Constraints</strong> — the actual limits, not symptoms</span></div>
                <div class="axis-item"><span class="arrow">↓</span><span><strong>Frameworks</strong> — reusable models that explain reality</span></div>
                <div class="axis-item"><span class="arrow">↓</span><span><strong>Systems</strong> — applied frameworks that outlast people</span></div>
                <div class="axis-item"><span class="arrow">↓</span><span><strong>Meaning</strong> — understanding that arrives after structure</span></div>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.7;">
                The audit isolates the constraint. The framework makes it reusable. The system makes it permanent.<br />
                Meaning is what remains.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="reveal" style="padding-top: 90px;">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ धीः क्रियया सम्पद्यते ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Protocol</span>
            <h2>How I Work</h2>
            <div class="process-grid reveal-stagger">
                <div class="node"><div><h4>01 — Diagnose</h4><p style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0;">Isolate active data liabilities, pipeline constraints, and structural weaknesses.</p></div></div>
                <div class="node"><div><h4>02 — Clarify</h4><p style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0;">Separate deep root causes from superficial surface-level symptoms.</p></div></div>
                <div class="node"><div><h4>03 — Prioritize</h4><p style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0;">Determine precisely which configuration cleanups generate maximum impact.</p></div></div>
                <div class="node"><div><h4>04 — Implement</h4><p style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0;">Where appropriate, permanent custom structures are engineered post-diagnosis.</p></div></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="reveal" style="padding-top: 90px;">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ व्यवस्थायाः सत्यम् ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Interface Parameters</span>
            <div class="reading" style="margin-left: 0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                <h2>The Systems Audit</h2>
                <p>The Systems Audit examines how your business is structured, documented, and operated. The goal is simple: Identify the actual constraints limiting performance and provide a clear path forward.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="audit-grid">
                <div class="reveal-stagger">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--text-muted); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 0.3rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Areas Reviewed</h3>
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.8rem;" class="node"><div><h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Digital Presence</h3><ul class="structural" style="margin-top: 0;"><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Website Structure Mapping</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Core Navigation Optimization</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Content Architecture Alignment</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Conversion Pathways Verification</li></ul></div></div>
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.8rem;" class="node"><div><h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Knowledge Systems</h3><ul class="structural" style="margin-top: 0;"><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Operational Centralized Documentation</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs)</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Knowledge Layer Accessibility Metrics</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Structural Information Organization</li></ul></div></div>
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.8rem;" class="node"><div><h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Business Operations</h3><ul class="structural" style="margin-top: 0;"><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Lead Management Pipelines</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Client Onboarding Workflows</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Service Delivery Mechanisms</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Internal Task Routing Flow</li></ul></div></div>
                    <div class="node"><div><h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Automation Mechanics</h3><ul class="structural" style="margin-top: 0;"><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Manual Tasks Eradication Map</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Active Integration Gaps Isolation</li><li style="border-bottom: none; padding: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Repetitive Processes Cleanup</li></ul></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="reveal">
                    <div class="sticky-box">
                        <div class="param"><span class="param-label">Capacity Allocation</span><div class="param-value highlight">Maximum 3 Active Clients Per Month</div></div>
                        <div class="param"><span class="param-label">Validation Rules</span><div class="param-value" style="font-size: 1.4rem;">Every Audit Personally Reviewed By Aman</div></div>
                        <div class="param"><span class="param-label">Investment Boundary</span><div class="param-value">₹4,999</div></div>
                        <div class="param"><span class="param-label">Engagement Timeline</span><div class="param-value" style="font-size: 1.5rem;">7 Business Days</div></div>
                        <hr />
                        <div class="param">
                            <span class="param-label">Delivered Verified Assets</span>
                            <ul style="list-style: none; margin-top: 0.3rem;">
                                <li style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); padding: 0.1rem 0;">• Comprehensive Systems Audit Report</li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);">— Clear Structural Findings Log</li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);">— Prioritized Improvement Path</li>
                                <li style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); padding: 0.1rem 0; margin-top: 0.2rem;">• 60-Minute Architecture Review Session</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <a href="/work-with-aman/systems-audit" class="btn btn-block" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Request a Systems Audit</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="reveal" style="padding-top: 90px;">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ ऋतस्य सत्यम् ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Advisory Scope</span>
            <h2 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Systems I Help Build</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 650px;">Each system is engineered from first principles — not bolted on afterward. <span style="color: var(--accent);">For Bhārat, from Bhārat.</span></p>
            <div class="blueprint-grid reveal-stagger">
                <div class="blueprint-node"><h3>Digital Presence</h3><p>Structural nodes, intuitive navigation, clean asset display, and high-intent conversion paths — all aligned to your actual workflow.</p></div>
                <div class="blueprint-node"><h3>Knowledge Systems</h3><p>Codified operating data, structural SOP archives, centralized internal hubs, and friction‑free documentation rules that scale without chaos.</p></div>
                <div class="blueprint-node"><h3>Business &amp; Automation</h3><p>Streamlined workflows, clean onboarding logic, duplicate task eradication, and dependency cleanup that removes human bottlenecks.</p></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 70px; padding-bottom: 60px; border-bottom: none;" class="reveal">
        <div class="container reading">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ आरम्भः श्रेयस्करः ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Initiation</span>
            <h2>Ready to understand what's really happening?</h2>
            <p>Most structural operational problems become exceptionally easy to manage once the real constraint is made visible. Request a Systems Audit and start with objective understanding — <span style="color: var(--accent);">rooted in Sanatan principles, built for Indian businesses.</span></p>
            <a href="/work-with-aman/systems-audit" class="btn" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">Request a Systems Audit</a>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>